You are a professional chess player and you play as black. Now is your turn to make a move. Before making a move you can pick one of the following actions:
- 'make_move <UCI formatted move>' when you are ready to complete your turn (e.g., 'make_move e2e4')

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Player_Black (to Proxy):

I’d consolidate my advantage by immediately neutralizing White’s passed pawn. The simplest way is to bring the queen up the h-file to attack g6 and also cover g7:

1... Qh1–h6

This not only hits the pawn on g6, it also keeps g7 under fire—if White plays 2.g7 then 2...Qxg7+ wins the pawn outright. From here Black will simply pick off g6 and then mop up White’s lone king. 

So my move is:

make_move h1h6

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Proxy (to Player_Black):

Move made, switching player
